1. Resolved Resonance Parameters                                  2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
The resolved resonance energy range extended to 363.28 keV, and   2237 1451
the resonance parameters were updated [Oh08] based on             2237 1451
Mughabghab's compilation [Mu06].                                  2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
2. Cross Sections, MF3, MT16, 22, 28, 102, 103, 107               2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
First GNASH calculation was performed to the Ti48(n,xng) data     2237 1451
from GEANIE experiments [Da07], and extended the same             2237 1451
parametrization to other isotopes. The level density              2237 1451
parameters were often adjusted to reproduce experimental data     2237 1451
of (n,2n), (n,p), and (n,alpha) reactions if available.           2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
The neutron radiative capture cross section was evaluated         2237 1451
with the CoH and DSD codes. The gamma-ray strength function       2237 1451
was renormalized to reproduce experimental data in the            2237 1451
20 - 50 keV energy range.                                         2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
3. Covariances, MF33                                              2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
All covariance data were calculated with the KALMAN code.         2237 1451
Typical uncertainties obtained are 1-3 % for the total,           2237 1451
10-30 % for the capture, etc. The covariance data for             2237 1451
(n,d) and (n,t) are not given, because they are very small        2237 1451
cross sections.                                                   2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
4. Secondary particle spectra [Nov. 2010]                         2237 1451
                                                                  2237 1451
Since an energy balance problem has been reported, MF6, 12,       2237 1451
and 14 were updated by calculating the particle and gamma-ray     2237 1451
spectra with the CoH3 code.                                       2237 1451
